data.title: The Old Rectory Cottage, Spetchley, Worcestershire
data.meta_description: The Old Rectory Cottage is a Grade II listed building in Spetchley, Worcestershire, England. See why it was listed, view it on a map, see visitor comments and photos and share your own comments and photos of this building.
data.text:
Description

SPETCHLEY SPETCHLEY

1.

2301

The Old Rectory Cottage

(formerly listed as

Keepers Cottage)

SO 95 SE 4/768 11.2.65.

II

2.

C17, house with projecting wing at back. Timber frame, lath and plaster

or brick infilling. 1 storey and attics. Gable and gabled dormer. Gabled

porch. Casement windows. Picturesque, Ancient door with moulded wooden

jambs. Shutters on ground floor windows.

Listing NGR: SO8949554084
